00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,000
Did that parent and child return home?

269
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,000
yes.

270
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:55,000
But until this time

271
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:55,000
I left my 5-year-old sister alone at home...

272
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:58,000
Is it okay?

273
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Well, I guess each family has their own circumstances.

274
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:09,000
What do you think about sleeping pills?

275
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:14,000
I will pass this on to the center director.

276
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:14,000
The rest is for a professional organization to decide.

277
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
I understand.

278
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:21,000
But...but so what?

279
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,000
You don't understand, do you?

280
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:26,000
Are we done with treatment?

281
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,000
So

282
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,000
Can we really say that we were saved?

283
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:36,000
Besides the doctor getting rid of the disease

284
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:36,000
What are you saving?

285
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,000
(Shibukawa)

286
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,000
Were you taking benzodiazepine sleeping pills?

287
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:47,000
8 years old is 3rd grade, right? It's hard to imagine drinking it by mistake.

288
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Yeah...leaving my 5-year-old at home alone...

289
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,000
That's strange.

290
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:55,000
Speaking of local residents

291
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:55,000
I often hear children crying.

292
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Hit against Fuyuka-chan→

293
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,000
It was pretty tough.

294
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,000
(Yokomine) Hey.

295
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
What do you think, Officer Yokomine?

296
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Will the child guidance center take action?

297
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Hmm... that's all

298
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Isn't it about how far you move?

299
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
(sigh)

300
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,000
So I have no choice but to move.

301
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Two people know about the house, right?

302
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,000
(Shibukawa) Huh?

303
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,000
yeah?

304
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
Handling personal information outside of work

305
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
It's against the rules!

306
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Huh? Are you hanging out?

307
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Huh? Who!

308
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:31,000
Protecting children is more important than following rules.

309
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:31,000
Right?

310
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
That's true, but...

311
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,000
(Machi Nomiya) You talk in a very rough way.

312
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,000
(Shozo Gonno) You can't stop.

313
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Wait, that's fine.

314
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Young people are always right.

315
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:49,000
But there's more than one right thing.

316
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,000
(Natsumi) What do you think? Fuyuka.

317
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:53,000
(Fuyuka) Expensive! Fufufu….

318
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,000
That was good.

319
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,000
Hello.

320
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,000
(Fuyuka) Ah, hello!

321
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Hello. Don't you have asthma anymore?

322
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Is it okay to play outside?

323
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,000
(Fuyuka) Ah, it's a police officer.

324
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Oh! He remembered me.

325
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,000
a little bit! I get angry when I talk to people I don't know.

326
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:16,000
I'm not a stranger.

327
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:16,000
Natsumi-chan is my patient. Right?

328
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,000
…Yeah.

329
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,000
(Shibukawa) Hello.

330
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:24,000
Would you like to be friends with me?

331
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
yes. This is a present from me.

332
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,000
thank you.

333
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,000
(Shibukawa) You're welcome.

334
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,000
(Fuyuka) How much is this?

335
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,000
The policeman and the doctor →

336
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Don't you have a present? why?

337
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Hey Fuyuka!

338
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,000
That's a very harsh opinion.

339
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,000
yes. This is for Natsumi too.

340
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,000
No, it's okay.

341
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:45,000
(Shibukawa) Natsumi-chan and Fuyuka-chan

342
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:45,000
It's about your mother...

343
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,000
(Chiharu) Fuyuka!

344
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:50,000
(Fuyuka) It's mom! welcome home!

345
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,000
My sister has just been discharged from the hospital.

346
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,000
If you want to play, play alone!

347
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,000
(Fuyuka) I'm sorry...

348
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,000
(Natsumi) No!

349
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,000
I said let's go outside.

350
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:03,000
Hello Mr. Yamashita.

351
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:03,000
This is Haruki from Wangan Hospital.

352
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:07,000
(Chiharu) Is there something you need?

353
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Natsumi-chan, how are you feeling?

354
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,000
I'm taking half a day off today to watch it.

355
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Go home.

356
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,000
(Yokomine) Mother

357
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,000
You don't have to pull it that hard...

358
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,000
Please wait a moment!

359
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,000
(Chiharu) What is it!?

360
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Fuyuka-chan has a bruise on her arm.

361
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,000
Can you show me if I need treatment?

362
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,000
I just fell. Hey? Fuyuka.

363
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,000
(Fuyuka) Yesterday...

364
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,000
(Chiharu) Fuyuka!

365
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:37,000
(Shibukawa) You don't have to yell like that.

366
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:37,000
That's fine.

367
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:41,000
I hear a child crying

368
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:41,000
We have also received reports from nearby residents.

369
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:48,000
(Chiharu) Eh... wait.

370
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Are you saying I'm being abusive?

371
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:53,000
If I was raising a child

372
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:53,000
You might even yell, right?

373
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:58,000
And the medical record address.

374
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:58,000
If you came to see it without permission, you'd be in trouble.

375
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,000
I'll call the police.

376
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Mr. Yamashita

377
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:04,000
I left Fuyuka-chan at home →

378
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:07,000
This may be considered abandonment of the guardian!

379
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:07,000
(Shibukawa) Mr. Haruki, anything more than that...

380
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Hello, are you the police?

381
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Please come now.

382
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,000
My daughter's hospital doctor and some men I don't know...

383
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,000
Mr. Yamashita, let's talk!

384
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:15,000
This is really a big deal!

385
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:15,000
(Chiharu) Looked at the address on the medical record and barged in without permission...

386
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,000
Mr. Yamashita!

387
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,000
(Yokomine) Stop it, hey...

388
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:23,000
I did it again...

389
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:23,000
I said it completely too much.

390
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,000
I became a police officer

391
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:26,000
The police were called for the first time.

392
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Hahahaha…!

393
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,000
Sigh….

394
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,000
But it's amazing.

395
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,000
I can't do it.

396
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:43,000
I'm really sorry.

397
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:43,000
I ended up getting two people involved again.

398
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,000
(Yokomine) Well, it can't be helped!

399
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,000
Hey... Yeah.

400
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:51,000
Even if those people come, you can't talk to them.

401
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,000
(Chiharu) It's boring! Eat with chopsticks!

402
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:58,000
But it has a handle.

403
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:01,000
It stems! Because it’s a stem!

404
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:01,000
It's not the place to have it.

405
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,000
(Natsumi) Ah...

406
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,000
Ah...

407
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Don't spill it!

408
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Babies eat twice as cleanly!

409
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,000
(sound of roughly placing hands)

410
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,000
sorry….

411
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:24,000
(Chiharu) Natsumi, let Fuyuka drink this later.

412
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Even if I go to bed

413
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Don't sleep, I'll jump.

414
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
(Chiharu) Ah...

415
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
It would be no good if Natsumi drank it.

416
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:42,000
♬〜

417
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Sister, it's no good...

418
00:17:49,891 --> 00:17:53,891
(Iwao Tachikawa) I could almost hear you crying.

419
00:17:49,891 --> 00:17:53,891
It's not evidence!

420
00:17:53,891 --> 00:17:55,891
(sigh)

421
00:17:55,891 --> 00:17:57,891
Be prepared for punishment!

422
00:17:57,891 --> 00:18:00,891
yes! Sorry!

423
00:18:01,891 --> 00:18:04,891
(Hanamaki) This time

424
00:18:01,891 --> 00:18:04,891
Are you planning to become a child guidance center worker?

425
00:18:04,891 --> 00:18:07,891
what you are doing

426
00:18:04,891 --> 00:18:07,891
You've crossed the line!

427
00:18:07,891 --> 00:18:10,891
...I'm sorry.

428
00:18:10,891 --> 00:18:14,891
(Akiyoshi Takagi) In the right place

429
00:18:10,891 --> 00:18:14,891
I'm already reporting it here.

430
00:18:14,891 --> 00:18:17,891
Enough already!

431
00:18:17,891 --> 00:18:20,891
Or drive home?

432
00:18:17,891 --> 00:18:20,891
Don't be so reckless!

433
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:22,891
That's right. It is.

434
00:18:22,891 --> 00:18:24,891
Say “desu” once!

435
00:18:24,891 --> 00:18:28,891
Do you really understand?

436
00:18:24,891 --> 00:18:28,891
yes….

437
00:18:28,891 --> 00:18:31,891
But once I took on a patient,

438
00:18:28,891 --> 00:18:31,891
I can't leave it alone...

439
00:18:31,891 --> 00:18:34,891
You don't understand!

440
00:18:34,891 --> 00:18:40,891
You know, getting into the inner workings of patients who have been discharged from the hospital...

441
00:18:34,891 --> 00:18:40,891
That's not a doctor's job!

442
00:18:40,891 --> 00:18:45,891
Then those kids

443
00:18:40,891 --> 00:18:45,891
Who will save me?

444
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:50,891
(Takagi) If you say so.

445
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:50,891
We have 20,000 patients a year.

446
00:18:50,891 --> 00:18:54,891
Focusing on one patient

447
00:18:50,891 --> 00:18:54,891
Can the remaining patients be saved?

448
00:18:55,891 --> 00:18:57,891
Mr. Kiryu! Mr. Kageyama is being carried away!

449
00:18:57,891 --> 00:18:59,891
Huh...?

450
00:19:03,891 --> 00:19:06,891
(Emergency worker) I saw a colleague collapse in his room.

451
00:19:03,891 --> 00:19:06,891
Looks like you discovered it.

452
00:19:06,891 --> 00:19:09,891
Currently, no injuries are found on JCS20.

453
00:19:06,891 --> 00:19:09,891
Understood.

454
00:19:09,891 --> 00:19:11,891
Prioritize stabilization of ABC.

455
00:19:09,891 --> 00:19:11,891
(light) Yes!

456
00:19:11,891 --> 00:19:14,891
I'm glad I discovered it early.

457
00:19:14,891 --> 00:19:17,891
(Co-worker) Shizuka: I'm not the type of person to be absent without notice.

458
00:19:14,891 --> 00:19:17,891
I stopped by the house.

459
00:19:17,891 --> 00:19:19,891
(light) Is there something you are concerned about?

460
00:19:19,891 --> 00:19:23,891
(Coworker) My husband and I are in the middle of divorce mediation.

461
00:19:19,891 --> 00:19:23,891
It seems like they're fighting over custody.

462
00:19:23,891 --> 00:19:25,891
I'm being followed around

463
00:19:23,891 --> 00:19:25,891
Because I was being consulted at the company →

464
00:19:25,891 --> 00:19:27,891
I thought maybe...

465
00:19:27,891 --> 00:19:29,891
(lamp) I understand.

466
00:19:27,891 --> 00:19:29,891
Please wait here.

467
00:19:30,891 --> 00:19:32,891
Does Kageyama-san have any chronic illness?

468
00:19:30,891 --> 00:19:32,891
Did you know?

469
00:19:32,891 --> 00:19:35,891
(Colleague) No... I've never heard anything about it.

470
00:19:36,891 --> 00:19:39,891
Kageyama-san, I'll touch it.

471
00:19:41,891 --> 00:19:45,891
Mr. Kageyama, can you hear me? Mr. Kageyama.

472
00:19:45,891 --> 00:19:49,891
(Shiori Akai) Heart rate is 95 and blood pressure is 63 out of 103.

473
00:19:51,891 --> 00:19:53,891
Kageyama-san has regained consciousness!

474
00:19:55,891 --> 00:19:59,891
Do you understand this? Can you say your name?

475
00:20:01,891 --> 00:20:07,891
Oh... is that kid...? Sho...?

476
00:20:07,891 --> 00:20:11,891
My father is keeping it

477
00:20:07,891 --> 00:20:11,891
A lawyer will contact you.

478
00:20:16,891 --> 00:20:18,891
Mr. Kageyama.

479
00:20:18,891 --> 00:20:23,891
Same as last time

480
00:20:18,891 --> 00:20:23,891
You didn't just fall, right?

481
00:20:23,891 --> 00:20:28,891
Have you had a serious injury before?

482
00:20:28,891 --> 00:20:31,891
For example, on the head.

483
00:20:31,891 --> 00:20:36,891
Before getting married...

484
00:20:36,891 --> 00:20:41,891
About 7 years ago →

485
00:20:41,891 --> 00:20:45,891
I suffered a brain contusion in a traffic accident.

486
00:20:47,891 --> 00:20:51,891
But it's really okay now.

487
00:20:56,891 --> 00:21:01,891
(Momoyama) Ah... it's an MRI image.

488
00:20:56,891 --> 00:21:01,891
You can see the scars from an old brain contusion.

489
00:21:01,891 --> 00:21:06,891
Is this the reason why I keep falling over?

490
00:21:01,891 --> 00:21:06,891
(Momoyama) That's right.

491
00:21:06,891 --> 00:21:09,891
Possibly post-traumatic epilepsy.

492
00:21:09,891 --> 00:21:14,891
Aftereffects of a traffic accident

493
00:21:09,891 --> 00:21:14,891
It may become apparent after several years.

494
00:21:14,891 --> 00:21:16,891
No doubt about it.

495
00:21:22,891 --> 00:21:24,891
(sound of door opening)

496
00:21:24,891 --> 00:21:26,891
Thank you for your hard work.

497
00:21:24,891 --> 00:21:26,891
Ou.

498
00:21:30,891 --> 00:21:35,891
That feeling... I'm not mentally prepared.

499
00:21:39,891 --> 00:21:42,891
This was told to me by the center director.

500
00:21:42,891 --> 00:21:48,891
Focusing on one patient

501
00:21:42,891 --> 00:21:48,891
Can the other patients be saved?

502
00:21:48,891 --> 00:21:50,891
Hahaha….

503
00:21:50,891 --> 00:21:55,891
...So, did Haruka-chan agree?

504
00:21:56,891 --> 00:21:59,891
I have no choice but to do it.

505
00:21:59,891 --> 00:22:01,891
The patient is not alone...

506
00:22:01,891 --> 00:22:04,891
Oh?

507
00:22:04,891 --> 00:22:09,891
Haruka-chan was still a trainee in internal medicine.

508
00:22:04,891 --> 00:22:09,891
What you said to me →

509
00:22:09,891 --> 00:22:12,891
Have you forgotten already?

510
00:22:12,891 --> 00:22:18,891
♬〜

511
00:22:18,891 --> 00:22:21,891
(sound of door opening)

512
00:22:21,891 --> 00:22:25,891
His eyes looked the same as back then.

513
00:22:26,891 --> 00:22:33,891
(woman crying)

514
00:22:33,891 --> 00:22:38,891
Why at a time like this?

515
00:22:33,891 --> 00:22:38,891
Were you the only one there?

516
00:22:38,891 --> 00:22:46,891
♬〜

517
00:22:46,891 --> 00:22:49,891
I'm sorry...

518
00:22:50,891 --> 00:22:54,891
(cry)

519
00:22:54,891 --> 00:23:08,891
♬〜

520
00:23:08,891 --> 00:23:13,891
I heard that the patient passed away.

521
00:23:13,891 --> 00:23:19,891
brought to the rescue center

522
00:23:13,891 --> 00:23:19,891
I was also in surgery.

523
00:23:20,891 --> 00:23:23,891
Are you sad?

524
00:23:25,891 --> 00:23:30,891
No... it's frustrating.

525
00:23:30,891 --> 00:23:34,891
Oh...

526
00:23:30,891 --> 00:23:34,891
Are you crying out of frustration? Haha….

527
00:23:35,891 --> 00:23:37,891
A trainee doctor?

528
00:23:40,891 --> 00:23:44,891
This is Haruki Haruki!

529
00:23:44,891 --> 00:23:47,891
I decided!

530
00:23:44,891 --> 00:23:47,891
yeah?

531
00:23:47,891 --> 00:23:51,891
I'm not going to become an internist.

532
00:23:47,891 --> 00:23:51,891
Become a lifesaving doctor!

533
00:23:51,891 --> 00:23:53,891
Why?

534
00:23:53,891 --> 00:23:57,891
I want to save everyone!

535
00:23:57,891 --> 00:23:59,891
That's why I became a doctor.

536
00:24:00,891 --> 00:24:06,891
Haruka-chan... you'll become a good doctor.

537
00:24:06,891 --> 00:24:20,891
♬〜

538
00:24:20,891 --> 00:24:23,891
(Shibukawa) Did you get angry after all?

539
00:24:23,891 --> 00:24:25,891
Solid.

540
00:24:25,891 --> 00:24:27,891
Aloy, are you going?

